        <mxCell id="kPV_PHt50KahIQ7stYgY-22" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;Databricks uses the concept of external locations to use storage accounts. An external location is a pairing of storage account path and a managed identity to access it. The managed identity is used by Databricks as a proxy for access to the storage account.&amp;nbsp; All access to the external path are managed by Databricks and must obey the ACLs that are in place.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div style=&quot;text-align: left;&quot;&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;background-color: transparent; color: light-dark(rgb(0, 0, 0), rgb(255, 255, 255));&quot;&gt;The storage for the tables will be defined at the catalog level, which will be set to a external location on the target storage account.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;" vertex="1">
          <mxGeometry height="180" width="390" x="392" y="100" as="geometry" />
        </mxCell>
        <mxCell id="kPV_PHt50KahIQ7stYgY-23" parent="1" style="rounded=1;whiteSpace=wrap;html=1;" value="Using serverless compute, any client is able to query the delta tables." vertex="1">
